# Accessibility Standards

## Web (ARIA + Semantic HTML)

### Use semantic elements first — ARIA only when no semantic element exists

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
<button onClick={handleDelete}>Delete</button>
<nav>...</nav>
<main>...</main>
<header>...</header>
```

❌ **BAD — div/span acting as interactive elements:**

```typescript
<div onClick={handleDelete}>Delete</div>  // not keyboard accessible
<span onClick={openMenu}>Menu</span>
```

### Icon-only buttons must have a label

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
<button aria-label="Delete item" onClick={handleDelete}>
  <TrashIcon />
</button>

// ❌ BAD — screen reader announces nothing useful
<button onClick={handleDelete}><TrashIcon /></button>
```

### Images

```typescript
<img src={photo} alt="User profile photo" />   // descriptive
<img src={decorativeBg} alt="" />              // empty alt for decorative images
```

### Form fields must have labels

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — label associated via htmlFor
<label htmlFor="title">Title</label>
<input id="title" value={form.title} onChange={...} />

// ✅ GOOD — aria-label when no visible label
<input aria-label="Search" placeholder="Search..." />

// ❌ BAD — placeholder is not a label
<input placeholder="Title" />
```

### Focus management

- Modals must trap focus while open and restore focus to the trigger on close
- Use `autoFocus` on the first interactive element inside a modal

## Mobile (React Native)

### All touchable elements need an accessibility label

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
<TouchableOpacity
  accessibilityLabel="Delete item"
  accessibilityRole="button"
  onPress={handleDelete}
>
  <Ionicons name="trash" />
</TouchableOpacity>

// ✅ GOOD — text content auto-announces, but role still needed for icons
<TouchableOpacity accessibilityRole="button" onPress={handleEdit}>
  <Text>Edit</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

### Common accessibilityRole values

| Element | Role |
|---------|------|
| Buttons | `"button"` |
| Links | `"link"` |
| Text inputs | `"none"` (TextInput handles it) |
| Images | `"image"` |
| Toggle/switch | `"switch"` |
| Tab bar item | `"tab"` |

### Loading and state announcements

```typescript
<ActivityIndicator accessibilityLabel="Loading items" />

// For dynamic content updates
<View accessibilityLiveRegion="polite">
  {statusMessage && <Text>{statusMessage}</Text>}
</View>
```

## Both Platforms — Key Rules

1. Every interactive element without visible text needs a label (`aria-label` / `accessibilityLabel`)
2. Color alone must never be the only way to convey information — pair with text or icon
3. Minimum touch target size on mobile: **44×44pt**
4. Test with VoiceOver (iOS) or TalkBack (Android) for mobile; keyboard navigation + screen reader for web
